{"id":86,"date":"2022-03-22T11:55:51","date_gmt":"2022-03-22T11:55:51","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/?p=86"},"modified":"2022-03-29T16:36:50","modified_gmt":"2022-03-29T15:36:50","slug":"is-there-really-a-silver-lining-to-icks","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/is-there-really-a-silver-lining-to-icks\/","title":{"rendered":"Is There Really a Silver lining to &#8220;Icks&#8221;?"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\"><em><strong>Whether you think &#8220;icks&#8221; are silly or not, good or bad, is there really a silver lining to getting the &#8220;ick&#8221;?<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"682\" src=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/pexels-mentatdgt-1399289-2-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-421\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/pexels-mentatdgt-1399289-2-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/pexels-mentatdgt-1399289-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/pexels-mentatdgt-1399289-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/pexels-mentatdgt-1399289-2-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/pexels-mentatdgt-1399289-2.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><figcaption>Image provided by <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pexels.com\/photo\/man-standing-in-front-of-woman-1399289\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.pexels.com\/photo\/man-standing-in-front-of-woman-1399289\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Mentatdgt from Pexels<\/a>.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Deriving from the sixth season of <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.itv.com\/loveisland\" target=\"_blank\">\u201cLove Island\u201d<\/a>&nbsp;U.K., the \u201cick\u201d hit social media by storm, making everyone question what our \u201cicks\u201d are. &nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The unofficial term, by <a href=\"https:\/\/www.urbandictionary.com\/author.php?author=sarahchasauce\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.urbandictionary.com\/author.php?author=sarahchasauce\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sarahchsauce<\/a> on Urban dictionary, defines an \u201cick\u201d as \u201csomething someone does that is an instant turn-off for you, making you instantly hate the idea of being with them romantically\u201d. But the \u201cick\u201d goes deeper than just a sexual turn off, with those feeling the \u201cick\u201d left to pick up the pieces of a now broken attraction.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may be wondering if you ever felt an \u201cick\u201d and whether they are really that serious. Well, let us all get into a pair of hypothetical shoes: you are on a wonderful date with a steaming hot guy (or girl), they open all the doors for you, lead an amazing conversation. You even start to think there is a second date upon the horizon when suddenly, they make that one move.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\"><p>&#8220;I said i got the ick&#8230; maybe I&#8217;m being too harsh&#8221; <\/p><cite><a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/priyagopaldas\/?hl=en\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/priyagopaldas\/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Priya Gopaldas<\/a> on Love Island 2021 (Video Below).<\/cite><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"The boys tell Brett Priya&#039;s got the &#039;ick&#039; | Love Island 2021\" width=\"580\" height=\"326\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/zd94u6o8QF0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><figcaption>Video provided by <a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=zd94u6o8QF0\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=zd94u6o8QF0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Love Island on YouTube<\/a><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Can An &#8220;Ick&#8221; Be?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cIcks\u201d are a very subjective discussion. Perhaps, they took a drink from a glass and all you could notice was their mouth open, chugging that water down through the glass. Or maybe they said <em>Mayonnaise<\/em> like \u201cman-aze\u201d or, all of a sudden, you picture them running up the stairs on all fours.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>An \u201cick\u201d is something that personally makes any possibility of a second date or some form of attraction, whether that is mental or sexual depleted.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\ud83d\udd25 FIRST LOOK \ud83d\udd25<br><br>Priya confides in the girls as she gets the ick, but it isn&#39;t long before the news makes it back to Brett&#8230; plus it&#39;s time to find out the results of the public vote and see whose time on the island is over <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/hashtag\/LoveIsland?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#LoveIsland<\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/MfXqx2FtDp\">pic.twitter.com\/MfXqx2FtDp<\/a><\/p>&mdash; Love Island (@LoveIsland) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/LoveIsland\/status\/1427300011394600963?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">August 16, 2021<\/a><\/blockquote><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script>\n<\/div><figcaption>Tweet posted by <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/LoveIsland\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/LoveIsland\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Love Island <\/a>on Twitter 16th August 2021<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Do &#8220;Icks&#8221; Mean?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from the unofficial Urban Dictionary definition, what do \u201cicks\u201d mean when they happen?&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You could say \u201cicks\u201d ultimately save us from a failed marriage. \u201cThe ick is different to just doubting whether you want to be with somebody,\u201d said Gurpreet Singh in an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cosmopolitan.com\/uk\/love-sex\/relationships\/a30699470\/the-ick\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">interview<\/a> with Cosmopolitan. \u201cThe ick is much more repulsive. It is a very strong gut reaction.\u201d &nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our body essentially gives us a warning sign that it is not meant to be.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the case of your date saying Mayonnaise like \u201cman-aze\u201d however, it could just be a friendly reminder that there are some things that will irritate you about this person. Which is normal!&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1021\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920-1021x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-422\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920-1021x1024.jpg 1021w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920-768x770.jpg 768w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920-1532x1536.jpg 1532w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920-1600x1604.jpg 1600w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920-1200x1203.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-g45a07519c_1920.jpg 1915w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1021px) 100vw, 1021px\" \/><figcaption>Image provided by <a href=\"https:\/\/pixabay.com\/illustrations\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-shouting-5740594\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/pixabay.com\/illustrations\/angry-wife-on-smartphone-shouting-5740594\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Azmeyart-design on Pixabay<\/a><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Are \u2018ick\u2019s important?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Just how \u2018icks\u2019 are subjective to personal standards, whether they are important or not is down to how you feel. Will the way they say something, do something or not do something be a deal-breaker or not.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, some cases are more extreme than others. Someone not washing their hands before eating or chewing with their mouth open may be a deal-breaker for most of us but, pronunciation may not be the end of the world for most of us.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Can Some &#8220;icks&#8221; be Ridiculous?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Usually, when things go viral online, they get blown way out of proportion. The topic of the \u201cick\u201d is no exception.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>From getting the \u201cick\u201d because he used a <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.tiktok.com\/@shxtsngigs\/video\/7042324235494149382\" target=\"_blank\">chocolate box menu to pick a chocolate from a selection box<\/a> to <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.tiktok.com\/@shxtsngigs\/video\/7047521143514795269\" target=\"_blank\">sitting in the wrong seat at a cinema and getting told to move<\/a>, there are sometimes silly agreements on what an \u201cick\u201d can be. But really, no \u201cick\u201d is ridiculous! We feel what we feel, and we get the \u201cick\u201d because we got an \u201cick\u201d.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"512\" src=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/mindfulness-g369578183_1280-1024x512.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-423\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/mindfulness-g369578183_1280-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/mindfulness-g369578183_1280-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/mindfulness-g369578183_1280-768x384.png 768w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/mindfulness-g369578183_1280-1200x600.png 1200w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/mindfulness-g369578183_1280.png 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><figcaption>Image provided by <a href=\"https:\/\/pixabay.com\/vectors\/mindfulness-brain-heart-mind-body-5371476\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/pixabay.com\/vectors\/mindfulness-brain-heart-mind-body-5371476\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">GDJ on Pixabay<\/a><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Is There a Silver Lining?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While \u201cicks\u201d are subjective, there is no doubt we all get them. Although this may be a revolutionary discovery, men also get them. The unseen benefit is that we are, once again, all in the same boat! It is okay to get them, as &#8220;icks\u201d are part of being human.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Discussions around our \u201cicks\u201d going viral online not only have sparked up a conversation between people agreeing and disagreeing, but they have also led to a lot of us being educated. &nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, someone who had an \u201cick\u201d over sweating may learn that there are certain diseases such as hyperhidrosis, which a person who sweats abnormally might suffer from.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Forums, such as our Reddit post below, are great places to discuss your own \u201cicks\u201d, find out new ones and become more educated. What do you think? Do &#8220;icks&#8221; really have a silver lining?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-reddit wp-block-embed-reddit\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"reddit-embed-bq\" style=\"height:316px\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.reddit.com\/r\/AskWomen\/comments\/snj6a4\/what_are_some_of_the_icks_you_cannot_ignore\/\">What are some of the \u2018icks\u2019 you cannot ignore?<\/a><br> by<a href=\"https:\/\/www.reddit.com\/user\/baddietruther\/\">u\/baddietruther<\/a> in<a href=\"https:\/\/www.reddit.com\/r\/AskWomen\/\">AskWomen<\/a><\/blockquote><script async src=\"https:\/\/embed.reddit.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"UTF-8\"><\/script>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Whether you think &#